  <title translate="true">Farm Allotment Dialog Box</title>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1"><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">Farm Allotment Dialog Box</text></para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">The </text><text styleclass="Strong" translate="true">Farm Allotment</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> dialog box is used to specify an surface-water allotment height (</text><text styleclass="Strong" translate="true">ALLOTSW</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">) when </text><text styleclass="Strong" translate="true">Surface water allotment (</text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Surface_Water_Flags" anchor="IALLOTSW" styleclass="Strong" translate="true">IALLOTSW</link><text styleclass="Strong" translate="true">)</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> is set to </text><text styleclass="Strong" translate="true">Equal (1)</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">. The dialog box is displayed by selecting </text><text styleclass="Strong" translate="true">Model|Farm Process|Farm Allotment...</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> This is a measure of the total amount of water available for delivery to all of the farms.</text></para>
  </body>
